.SHNAME
.B simple_shell
- Simple shell create in c to interact with linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
hsh [options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Shell is a UNIX term for the interactive user interface with an operating system.
The shell is the layer programming that understands
and executes the commands a user enters. In some systems, the shell is called a
command interpreter. A shell usually implies an interface
with a command syntax

.B Overview

The simple shell is a command that reads lines from either a file or the
terminal, interprets them, and generally executes other commands. It is the
program that is started when a user logs into the system. It incorporates
many features to aid t oboth interactive and non-interactive use
(shell scripts). that is, commands can be typed directly to the running simple
shell or can be put into a file, which can
.SH Return value

Always 0 for success, other number meabs failure.

.SH PATH

It will look inside al directions in PATH env variable for executable.

.SH

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options wille be typed after the main command followed by a space and 
a '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLE

[command] [options]
$ le -l

.SH BUGS
Single space required after argument.

